The paper proposes a novel deep network architecture for lifelong learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper focuses on the efficient training of the network in an online manner, which suggests a focus on reinforcement learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also validates the proposed architecture on multiple public datasets, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper mentions the use of timestamping to prevent semantic drift, which suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
